Implemented on 2026-04-10

Completed
- Moved the event bus into `src/shared/events` behind a replaceable transport abstraction.
- Removed direct `EventEmitter2` usage from workflow-facing services and routed bus publishes through the shared event bus.
- Added explicit event subscribers in both modules:
  - conversation subscriber for `WORKFLOW_ASK_OPTIONS` and `WORKFLOW_NO_OPTIONS_FOUND`
  - workflow subscriber for conversation/workflow lifecycle events
- Removed the old competing wildcard workflow subscriber path from module wiring so events are not processed twice.
- Verified `WORKFLOW_PROCESSED` questions emit `WORKFLOW_ANSWER_RECEIVED` through the real bus.
- Implemented workflow-driven option publishing with action handlers:
  - `HTTP_GET`
  - `EMIT_EVENT`
  - `WORKFLOW_ASK_OPTIONS`
  - `WORKFLOW_NO_OPTIONS_FOUND`
- Fixed action execution so custom workflow events can be emitted while `ACTION_COMPLETED` still advances the workflow.
- Enabled nested `resultMapping` payloads so workflows can emit:
  - `conversationId`
  - `question.text`
  - `question.options`
  - `metadata`
- Implemented dynamic conversation-side option handling and normalized workflow-provided options from raw API records.
- Fixed workflow option persistence so the selected option value becomes the saved valid answer.
- Conversation now advances to the next real questionnaire question after workflow option selection instead of re-asking the original workflow question.
- Added a built-in seeded workflow and questionnaire for:
  - customer name
  - facility lookup via workflow
  - appointment date
- Added integration/regression coverage for:
  - normal questions still work
  - workflow-backed dynamic option lookup
  - workflow not triggered for non-workflow questions
  - workflow submission flow still works
  - no duplicate `WORKFLOW_ASK_OPTIONS` emission in the new path

Important bug fixes
- `HTTP_POST` previously executed `axios.get`; fixed HTTP method handling via `axios.request`.
- Added legacy compatibility for `HTTP_REQUEST` and `mapping`.
- Fixed condition evaluation so workflow expressions can reference workflow state directly.
- Fixed event sequencing by removing async fire-and-forget subscriber registration that allowed race conditions between steps.
- Fixed `maxTransitionsPerRun` handling to use event-chain sequence metadata instead of a state counter that accumulated forever.
- Fixed conversation schema persistence for `workflowInstanceId`.
- Fixed workflow option outbound response creation to use a valid ObjectId question id.
- Fixed question processor default processed answer behavior for non-API questions.
- Fixed API-processed answer handling regression in question processor.

Validation
- `npm run build`
- `npm run test:e2e -- test/modules/conversation/conversation.e2e-spec.ts test/modules/conversation/workflow-submission.e2e-spec.ts test/modules/conversation/workflow-dynamic-options.e2e-spec.ts test/modules/workflow/workflow-processing.e2e-spec.ts`

Open notes
- The shared event bus currently uses the in-memory transport adapter by default.
- The transport boundary is now isolated so Redis/Kafka can replace it later without rewriting conversation/workflow business logic.
